{"word":"εὐνάω","slug":"εὐνάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐνάω</b></el> <el>(εὐνάω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εὐνή'><el>εὐνή</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> for <a href='S:εὐνάζω'><el>εὐνάζω</el></a>: \n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to lay</i> or <i>place in ambush</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to lay asleep, lull to sleep</i>, <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>εὔνησε γόον</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to lie asleep</i>, of a dog, <i>to lie kennelled</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: of the winds, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}